üß© Overview

This repository contains my solution for the Image Matching Challenge 2025, a large-scale computer vision competition focused on grouping images into coherent 3D scenes and reconstructing accurate camera poses.

The task advances Structure-from-Motion (SfM) and image clustering at scale, addressing a fundamental challenge: how to determine which images belong together when online image collections are noisy, unstructured, and visually ambiguous.

Real-world datasets often contain unrelated or visually confusing images, making classical SfM pipelines brittle. This competition pushes toward robust, scalable systems capable of handling:

Similar-looking but distinct scenes

Outlier images

Missing GPS/metadata

Challenging lighting, perspective, and photometric variations

My approach focuses on robust image grouping, pose estimation, and hybrid registration heuristics, balancing precision and recall as measured by the competition‚Äôs harmonic scoring metric.

